    "This finer granularity enhances efficiency and precision in identifying vulnerabilities.",
    "For instance, Du et al. [54] proposed the LEOPARD framework which uses program metrics and avoids the need for prior knowledge of known vulnerabilities.",
    "This framework seeks to overcome the limitations of machine learning-based methods, which struggle with imbalanced data, and pattern-based methods, which require prior knowledge.",
    "LEOPARD was evaluated on a benchmark comprising 11 real-world open-source projects, including BIND, FFmpeg, Linux, OpenSSL, and Wireshark written in C and C++.",
    "LEOPARD's metric-based grouping and ranking can serve as a pre-filtering step, potentially enhancing the efficiency and accuracy of DL models."
